<!-- Comments are shown as below
  ****************************************************************************************************
	* All resources would be stored in folders according to its media type
	* Logoes are stored in image, the ID defined for logoes are added with a pre-fix of "logo-"
	* For example, logo with Id of "09" is configured as:
	* logo-09 = "logo_small.jpeg"
	
	* Format:
	* resource_id = file_name.extension | Fullscreen; Loop; Centeral; Resize(width, height); Orignal; Single
	* Examples:
	* 000 = 000.jpg | f                 => stretch to right/bottom from cursor's position
	* 010 = 010.mpeg | l ; f            => play in infinite loops in full screen mode
	* 100 = 100.jpeg | r(100, 125)      => resize
	* 110 = 110.mpeg | r(200, 125); c   => 110.mpeg is displayed at the center of screen after resized to width/height of 200/125
	* 111 = 111.jpeg | o                => use orignal size
	* beep = beep.wav | l               => beep.wav is played repeatedly till the current screen is switched out
	* A009 = DAUDIO09.WAV | s           => beep.wav is not played repeatly even all medias are set to be played repeatedly
	
	* A special resource "default" is used to set default configurations that is generally applicable for all resources.
	* Example:
	* default = default.jpg | f; l      => by default, all resources are fullscreen, and loop
	
	* remarks:
	* * Centeral is not supported yet;

	* =============================================================
	* standard resources referenced from screen scripts
	* =============================================================
  *****************************************************************************************************
-->
